  m_Name: StoryCard_18_WendTruth
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.StoryCardData
  _id: wend_truth
  _act: Act III
  _scene: Scene 3
  _title: The Wend's True Course
  _subtitle: Wendlight grows where the river used to flow.
  _body: "The journal in the cottage names a mushroom that fruits only on land where
    clean water once ran. Wren walks the dry bed of the old Wend at dawn and the
    Wendlight is already there \u2014 pale, brittle, glowing faintly in the half-light.
    The Wend's course-shift was not weather. The deforestation upstream was the work
    of Lord Aldric's woodcutters."
  _wrenNote: For three winters this village has called the river's leaving an act
    of God. It was an act of accounting. I do not know yet what to do with that.
  _beats:
  - Wendlight mushrooms reveal the river's old course.
  - The course-shift was caused by deforestation upstream.
  - Lord Aldric's name enters the story for the first time as a cause, not a backdrop.
  _image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: f0e44ace9ce274b0d90bd231e1d98c25, type: 3}
  _unlockAt: 17
  _questId: wendlightFound
  _displayNameId: story.wend_truth.title
